^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|As usual a few suggestions and comments. First let us examine Dee's rebid options. She has a really good hand. 3H is really a bit too weak as a rebid. She has 17 HCP, 2 length points, and 1 quality suit = 20. 3H shows 16 or 17 or so, and is not forcing. Dee has 2 other choices. One is to jump shift into her 3 card diamond suit, so bid 3D. Sometimes you have to do that. The other, which I like better is to bid 4H. Her suit meets the "singleton test." That means, she is willing to play in hearts opposite a singleton in partner's hand. If that is the case, you can consider your suit "self-sufficient."|
