^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Okay, lets discuss the auction a bit. As Patti mentioned, I do not believe in "rescuing" partner from a possible short minor. If you don't have six points or at least five with something worth saying, you should not worry about passing even with shortness in partner;s suit. First of all, there is little to worry about. Virtually all the time, partner has 4+ clubs. Partner only has three clubs less than 10% of the time, so if you have to guess, assume four clubs at least. |
