^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Okay, two things to discuss. Dee's bid and Patti's opening lead. First Dee's bid. She has a clear 3H bid. When partner opens a Weak-2, and you have 3 card support, by the Law of Total Tricks you should always bid 3 unless you think game is possible. Of course then you should bid 2N. So, it is an automatic 3 bid over a Weak-2 with three card support even with few points, say six or so. |
